metadata.description: Johann Sebastian Bach was a German composer of the 18th century. Bach was famous for his religious music and keyboard works. His passion and talent for music was recognised at a young age. Bach loved playing the organ and became an organ virtuoso, recognised for his talent. His compositions were also recognised as some of the best of his time. Bach left a remarkable mark on the world of music and became a figure with a lasting influence on the history of music.
